cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.CL

This paper deals with the development of cost functions for training predictive deep learning models that aim to maximize the concordance correlation coefficient (CCC) while minimizing prediction errors. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the development of algorithms and models for machine learning tasks. The paper also uses data from the SEWA database, which deals with audio/visual emotion analysis, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with inter-rater agreement and performance metrics, which are topics covered in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CL (Computation and Language), respectively.
